ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think="Interesting - the BDD tests all pass, including `auth.steps.js`. That
means `auth.feature` must still exist. Let me check its contents.\n\nNow let me 
check some more potential issues:\n1. `make lint` fails for `packages/shared-typ
es` due to missing ESLint config\n2. Need to check Flutter analyze\n3. Need to c
heck `make generate-types` and `make check-contract-sync`\n4. The webhook signat
ure validation in `content-moderation.controller.ts` is not using HMAC - compari
ng raw strings is insecure\n5. The `docker-compose.yml` has `depends_on` with `c
ondition: service_healthy` for api on mysql/redis, but `api` doesn't wait proper
ly - it just starts immediately. Actually `depends_on` with `condition` is a Doc
ker Compose v3.8 feature, but it only guarantees container start order, not serv
ice readiness. However, the API container starts `npm run start:dev` which shoul
d handle connection retries.\n6. The `Makefile` has `make dev` using `docker-com
pose up --build -d mysql redis api admin` but `docker-compose` v2 uses `docker c
ompose` (space, not hyphen). However, `docker-compose` may still work if install
ed.\n7. Looking at the diff, old `.githooks/pre-commit` and `.githooks/pre-push`
were deleted and replaced with `.husky/pre-commit`. The new `.husky/pre-commit` 
just runs `npx lint-staged`. But `lint-staged` is configured in root `package.js
on` to run `eslint --fix`, `dart format`, and `prettier --write`. The PRD says i
t should check docs in CI, but the pre-commit hook doesn't run `make check-docs`
anymore (the old `.githooks/pre-commit` did). This is a regression.\n8. The `Mak
