    type='think',
    think='The `openapi-generator-cli` fails because it can\'t download the jar 
file due to SSL certificate issues in this environment. But the existing generat
ed code was presumably committed to the repo. The `check-contract-sync.sh` scrip
t suppresses errors with `> /dev/null 2>&1 || true`, so the generator silently f
ails and produces an empty temp directory, which then differs from the existing 
generated code.\n\nThis is a CI/environment issue, not a code issue per se. In a
normal CI environment with proper internet access, the generator would work. How
ever, the script\'s use of `> /dev/null 2>&1 || true` is bad practice because it
masks real failures. If the generator fails for any reason (not just network), t
he check script would report "out of sync" rather than "generation failed".\n\nB
ut since this is an infrastructure review and the PR is about setting up the too
ling, this is an important observation.\n\nLet me now look at what files were ac
tually added/changed and summarize my findings. I should also check if there are
any NestJS module structure violations.\n\nLet me check the `all-exceptions.filt
er.ts` and `logging.interceptor.ts` for completeness.',
    encrypted=None
)
